    "Current invasions of new technologies are the result of the interplay of past events and processes (Kueffer, 2010b; Pyšek et al., 2010; Essl et al., 2011).",
    "The extension of knowledge in these fields is basic for resolving fundamental questions in invasion ecology of technologies and is associated with the accumulation of manifold and detailed information on invasions of particular technologies in different industries and over time.",
